tafsir[3]{c,v,t}:
  23,18,"And We sent down out of heaven water in measure and lodged it in the earth; and We are able to take it away."
  23,20,"and a tree issuing from the Mount of Sinai that bears oil and seasoning for all to eat."
  23,25,"He is naught but a man bedevilled; so wait on him for a time."